Vice President Mike Pence spoke with Prime Minister Nechirvan Barzani of Iraq's Kurdistan Regional Government. They discussed Iran's recent rocket attacks into the Kurdistan region and condemned them as an attempt to threaten and destabilize Iraq's closest neighbor. They also talked about the Kurdish position during government formation and reaffirmed the strategic partnership between the Kurds and the United States. Prime Minister Barzani expressed gratitude for U.S. support in the fight against ISIS and emphasized the need for further cooperation between the two countries. Vice President Pence congratulated the Prime Minister on initiatives to promote religious freedom in the KRG and they agreed to work closely on helping Iraq's persecuted religious communities return to their ancestral homes.